        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 1:43PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 143 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Aberdeen, or 8 miles south of Southern Pines,
moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southern Pines, Carthage, Pinehurst, Aberdeen, Hoffman, Whispering
Pines, Pinebluff, Foxfire, Taylortown, and Vass.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
